00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:33,876
What is the brain?

13
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:37,317
If you don' t know that,
you've forgotten how to think.

14
00:01:37,480 --> 00:01:40,951
You see, the brain is many things.

15
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:45,957
It's a calculator,
a dictionary, a battery,

16
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:50,000
a camera, a TV and radio.

17
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:54,070
In fact, it's all of these things
and more.

18
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:58,632
Pretty smart for something that
resembles a garden cauliflower.

19
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:02,191
The brain is basically
a wrinkled bag of skin

20
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:06,036
filled with warm water,
veins and thought muscles.

21
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:12,472
Think of it as a kind of modified
heart, only with a mind or brain.

22
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:17,752
It sits atop the body issuing its
orders to the various components,

23
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:21,834
controlling our walking
and jumping,

24
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:25,555
eye-to-eye coordination.

25
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:30,840
Regulating our size.

26
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:37,559
In fact, pretty much everything
we do is governed by its decisions.

27
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:40,440
It's a right old bossyboots!

28
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:43,833
The opposite of the brain
is probably the bum.

29
00:02:44,480 --> 00:02:46,949
It's nowhere near as intelligent
as the brain.

30
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,440
It doesn' t have to be,

31
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:51,474
as it only needs to make
very basic calculations.

32
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:00,672
An experiment was carried out

33
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:04,277
to illustrate the effects
of brainial stimulation.

34
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,760
For this experiment,

35
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:09,550
we're going to use a small area
of our subject's brain

36
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:12,355
known as the broab.

37
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:14,832
Using a hand drill,

38
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,630
a small hole is formed
at the base of Nigel's skull.

39
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:25,910
You don' t have to be a brain
surgeon operate on the brain,

40
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,675
but you will need some training.

41
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:33,039
After all, you'd hardly call out
a hairdresser to fix a carburettor.

42
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:38,997
Now a thin probe is slowly inserted
into our hole

43
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:42,119
so that the probe probes the broab.

44
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:48,234
Observe the reaction and note
the results down in your copybook.

45
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:55,000
At first, Nigel appears
to experience some discomfort.

46
00:03:56,800 --> 00:04:00,589
But this soon gives way
to a feeling of elation.

47
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:07,710
And as we force the probe deeper,
it induces this reaction.

48
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:13,631
A feeling of wanting to sneeze
but being completely unable to.

49
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,313
If you're trying this experiment
for yourself,

50
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:20,359
be aware that the effect
is often permanent.

51
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,799
Write that down
in your copybook now.

52
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:30,356
