60
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:55,232
Don' t be a fool.

61
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:04,077
It's not just humans or animals
that have a brain.

62
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:06,755
Almost every living being has one.

63
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:14,037
If we look inside one of these
peas, we can see its tiny brain.

64
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:19,235
Look at the little ridges,

65
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:24,431
down which the pea sends
electrical impulses to other peas,

66
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:28,958
determining its daily duties
and its status in the pod.

67
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:33,395
Let's pop it back inside now,
and leave the pea be.

68
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:49,112
An experiment was carried out

69
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:52,956
to illustrate the brain's
powers of perception.

70
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:59,640
First, a human brain is lowered
gently into a solution of brine.

71
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:09,189
Next, we connect a 9-volt battery,

72
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:14,230
so an electrical current flows
through the brine into the brain.

73
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:19,999
Finally, a telephone line
is installed...

74
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:38,676
..and the experiment can begin.

75
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:42,312
We're going to set the brain
a simple problem,

76
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:45,040
so have your pen and paper ready.

77
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:52,637
Brain, how many nuts
are there in this jar?

78
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:57,840
The brain sets to work
until reaches its answer.

79
